description: The idea of the two page story sprang from the success of 8th Wonder Press‚Äôs previous anthologies. ‚ÄúWe started receiving so many incredible submissions that it became impossible to narrow them down,‚Äù explained Dubin. ‚ÄúThe solution was to challenge each creative team to work within a specific number of pages, and giving each story two pages really opened up the possibilities while increasing the urgency in each story.‚Äù Each of the three issues in Uncanny Adventures: Duo has a different theme, from sci-fi and fantasy to action/adventure, to an incredible all-humor issue. With 11 stories per issue, not only is the length of every story a novel device, but it allows for a wide range of diverse stories. In any given issue, stories can range from light to serious, poetic to literal, or cartoony to realistic. Literally every turn of the page gives the reader an opportunity to find something new.
name: Uncanny Adventures: Duo
